The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification in crowded public places, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method uses deep learning and attention mechanisms to address the occlusion problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves multi-task learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves generating artificial occlusions, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also involves addressing security and privacy concerns in public places, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
